  "title": "Digital Marketing Senior / Executive – Character Brand | Up to $4,500/month",
  "description": "<p>A leading lifestyle and character brand in Southeast Asia is seeking a <strong>creative and driven Digital Marketing Executive</strong> to grow its online and offline presence. This role is ideal for candidates with <strong>prior experience working with licensed character products or similar branded merchandise</strong>, who can bring passion and insight to brand campaigns.</p><p>📍 <strong>Location:</strong> Central area<br />🕰️ <strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday – Friday, 9:30 AM – 6:00 PM<br />💰 <strong>Salary:</strong> Up to $4,500/month (depending on experience)</p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Strategize, plan, and execute engaging content across <strong>social media channels and the company’s webpage</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Develop creative ideas, visuals, and copywriting that align with the <strong>brand identity</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with internal teams and external partners to enrich the content library and build digital portfolios.</p></li><li><p>Develop impactful campaigns, track KPIs (reach, followers, engagement) and prepare wrap-up reports.</p></li><li><p>Support <strong>event/product launches, offline campaigns, and in-store activations</strong> with integrated online-offline initiatives.</p></li><li><p>Assist the Marketing Manager in driving marketing strategy and update stakeholders (licensees, retailers, agents) regularly.</p></li><li><p>Track regional marketing and trade expenses, ensuring efficient use of budget and proper documentation.</p></li><li><p>Manage regional marketing assets and support administration tasks as needed.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements:</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s Degree / Diploma in Marketing, Business, Communications, or related field.</p></li><li><p>1–3 years’ experience in <strong>digital marketing, brand promotion, or marketing campaigns</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Experience with licensed character products, merchandise, or similar branded products</strong> is strongly preferred.</p></li><li><p>Ability to plan and execute <strong>digital marketing campaigns</strong> and content creation.</p></li><li><p>Strong multitasking skills and ability to meet tight deadlines.</p></li><li><p>Team player with the ability to operate independently; resourceful and proactive problem-solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Positive, outgoing, hands-on attitude with keen interest in character brands.</p></li><li><p>Confident communicator, able to liaise effectively with internal and external partners.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications.</p></li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p>Please include your availability, notice period and expected salary in your application.</p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em><br /></p><p>—</p><p>Annie Hoang (R25158747)</p><p>CREW by HRnet | HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd </p><p>EA24C2435</p>",
